            <div class='post' itemprop='articleBody'>
              <p>hello</p>
<p>I try to install redash in a Debian or Ubuntu virtual machine (which is a lxc proxmox container)<br>
and I always get these errors below when starting redis and postgres services</p>
<p>I guess it might come from the container ? Is there a workaround to make redash works in a lxc container?</p>
<p>thanks for help<br>
Maurice</p>
<p>%%%%%% trace %%%%<br>
docker-compose.yml  100%[===================&gt;]   1.05K  --.-KB/s    in 0s</p>
<p>2022-07-21 07:40:24 (41.1 MB/s) - ‚Äòdocker-compose.yml‚Äô saved [1076/1076]</p>
<p>Starting redash_redis_1    ‚Ä¶ error<br>
Starting redash_postgres_1 ‚Ä¶</p>
<p><strong>ERROR: for redash_redis_1  Cannot start service redis: b‚Äôfailed to create shim task: OCI runtime create failed: runc create failed: unable to start container process: error during container init: error mounting ‚Äúproc‚Äù to rootfs at ‚Äú/proc‚Äù: Starting redash_postgres_1 ‚Ä¶ error</strong></p>
<p><strong>ERROR: for redash_postgres_1  Cannot start service postgres: b‚Äôfailed to create shim task: OCI runtime create failed: runc create failed: unable to start container process: error during container init: error mounting ‚Äúproc‚Äù to rootfs at ‚Äú/proc‚Äù: mount proc:/proc (via /proc/self/fd/6), flags: 0xe: permission denied: unknown‚Äô</strong></p>
<p>ERROR: for redis  Cannot start service redis: b‚Äôfailed to create shim task: OCI runtime create failed: runc create failed: unable to start container process: error during container init: error mounting ‚Äúproc‚Äù to rootfs at ‚Äú/proc‚Äù: mount proc:/proc (via /proc/self/fd/6), flags: 0xe: permission denied: unknown‚Äô</p>
<p>ERROR: for postgres  Cannot start service postgres: b‚Äôfailed to create shim task: OCI runtime create failed: runc create failed: unable to start container process: error during container init: error mounting ‚Äúproc‚Äù to rootfs at ‚Äú/proc‚Äù: mount proc:/proc (via /proc/self/fd/6), flags: 0xe: permission denied: unknown‚Äô<br>
ERROR: Encountered errors while bringing up the project.<br>
